gobblin.data.management.copy.writer

Class TarArchiveInputStreamDataWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.data.management.copy.writer.FileAwareInputStreamDataWriter
      • gobblin.data.management.copy.writer.TarArchiveInputStreamDataWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FinalState, DataWriter<FileAwareInputStream>, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class TarArchiveInputStreamDataWriter
extends FileAwareInputStreamDataWriter
    An FileAwareInputStreamDataWriter to write archived InputStreams. The FileAwareInputStreamDataWriter.write(FileAwareInputStream) method receives a GZIPInputStream and converts it to a TarArchiveInputStream. Each TarArchiveEntry is then written to the FileSystem.

    • Method Detail

      • writeImpl

        public void writeImpl(FSDataInputStream inputStream,
                      Path writeAt,
                      CopyableFile copyableFile)
               throws IOException
        Untars the passed in FileAwareInputStream to the task's staging directory. Uses the name of the root TarArchiveEntry in the stream as the directory name for the untarred file. The method also commits the data by moving the file from staging to output directory.
        Overrides:
        writeImpl in class FileAwareInputStreamDataWriter
        Parameters:
        inputStream - FSDataInputStream whose contents should be written to staging path.
        writeAt - Path at which contents should be written.
        copyableFile - CopyableFile that generated this copy operation.
        Throws:
        IOException
        See Also:
        FileAwareInputStreamDataWriter.write(gobblin.data.management.copy.FileAwareInputStream)
